==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[maul]], [[mall]], and [[mawle]].

===Noun===
'''malle'''  (''plural:'' '''[[malles]]''')
# (''Weapon'') [[Category:Weapon]] A [[heavy]] [[hammer]] or [[beetle]], often made of [[wood]] or [[lead]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''': The is also an [[entry]] of two [[hundred]] [[Malles]] in a [[store]] [[house]] at Berwick. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 52.

[[Category:English nouns]]

